{{BLP IMDB refimprove|date=January 2011}} {{Infobox person | name = Jimmy Bennett | image = | imagesize = | caption = | birthname = James Michael Bennett | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1996|2|9}} | birth_place = [[Seal Beach, California]], [[United States|U.S.]] | occupation = Actor, Musician |yearsactive = 2002âpresent | homepage = }} '''James Michael "Jimmy" Bennett''' (born February 9, 1996) is an [[United States|American]] actor and musician. He is known for his roles as a [[child actor]] in ''[[Daddy Day Care]]'', ''[[Hostage (film)|Hostage]]'', ''[[Poseidon (film)|Poseidon]]'', and more recently in ''[[Orphan (film)|Orphan]]'' and as young [[James T. Kirk]] in ''[[Star Trek (film)|Star Trek]]''. He also starred in ''[[No Ordinary Family]]'' as JJ Powell, a teenager gifted with vast intelligence after a plane crash.
==Life and career== Bennett was born in [[Seal Beach, California]] and now lives with his parents and his sister in [[Huntington Beach, California]], where the family runs a [[hard rock]] themed [[crepe]] restaurant.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/tn-hbi-1230-pipeline-20101227,0,6959136.story | work=Chicago Tribune | first=Chris | last=Epting | title=In the Pipeline: Rock history is on the menu}}</ref><ref>http://lateenfestival.com/magazine/008/jimmybennett.html</ref><ref>http://www.fb101.com/Jimmy_Bennett.html</ref> When not acting, Bennett plays guitar and sings on his official YouTube channel. He also wrote and performed the song ''Summer Never Ends'' which can be heard at the end of ''[[Shorts (film)|Shorts]]''.<ref>http://us.imdb.com/title/tt1100119/soundtrack</ref>
Bennett appeared in nearly 30 [[television advertisement|commercials]]{{Citation needed|date=September 2009}}, as well as in [[episode]]s of the [[television]] [[television program|series]] ''[[The Guardian (TV series)|The Guardian]]'' and ''[[Strong Medicine]]'', before being [[Casting (performing arts)|cast]] in the [[Role (performing arts)|role]] "Tony", the boy who wants to be [[The Flash]], in the [[Eddie Murphy]] [[comedy]] ''[[Daddy Day Care]]''. He had smaller roles in the [[movie]]s ''[[Anchorman: The Legend of Ron Burgundy]]'' and "Arthur Hailey's Detective". He has also appeared in ''[[Judging Amy]]'', ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'' and ''[[Everwood]]'', and lent his voice to [[Fictional character|characters]] in the [[animated]] films ''[[The Polar Express (film)|The Polar Express]]'', ''[[Winnie the Pooh: Springtime with Roo]]'' and ''I Want a Dog for Christmas, Charlie Brown''. He has been [[nominated]] for [[Young Artist Awards]] five times.<ref name="imdb">{{cite web | title=IMDB | work=Awards for Jimmy Bennett (III) | url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm1497548/awards | accessdate=March 14, 2006}}</ref>
In 2005, Bennett appeared in the film ''[[Hostage (film)|Hostage]]'', where he starred with [[Bruce Willis]], and ''[[The Amityville Horror (2005 film)|The Amityville Horror]]'', where he played the role of the middle child of a family moving into a [[haunted house]]. The films were released in [[March 2005|March]] and [[April 2005|April]], respectively. He was called "Jimmy Two-Takes" on the set of "Hostage", because of his ability to deliver his lines perfectly.<ref>http://www.u-got-it.dk/data/1608582/Hostage%20Production%20Notes.doc</ref>
In February 2006, Bennett appeared in the thriller ''[[Firewall (movie)|Firewall]]'', where he played the son of [[Harrison Ford]]'s character. He also played an [[child abuse|abused]] boy in ''[[The Heart Is Deceitful Above All Things]]'', an [[independent film]] that was released a month after ''Firewall''. Also in 2006, he voiced [[Roo]] in the [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]]/[[Square-Enix]] video game ''[[Kingdom Hearts II]]'' and appeared in ''[[Poseidon (film)|Poseidon]]'', a remake of the 1972 film ''[[The Poseidon Adventure (1972 film)|The Poseidon Adventure]]''. His 2007 roles include ''South of Pico'', an independent film, and ''[[Evan Almighty]]'', a sequel to the 2003 film ''[[Bruce Almighty]]''. He appeared as a young [[James T. Kirk]] in the 2009 ''[[Star Trek (film)|Star Trek]]'' movie. He also starred in the 2009 film ''[[Orphan (film)|Orphan]]'' and the TV series ''[[No Ordinary Family]]''.<ref>http://www.ksitetv.com/jimmy-bennett-is-no-ordinary-son/</ref>
Bennett will also star in the upcoming film ''[[Bones (2010 film)|Bones]]'', featuring him alongside famed [[Ozzy Osbourne]] guitarist and Black Label Society frontman [[Zakk Wylde]]. Bones is described as a "heartbreaking coming-of-age story of four teens growing up in 1989 blue-collar New York, and the bond that would tie them together for life."
In August 2011, Bennett released his debut single "Over Again" and the accompanying music video.<ref>http://www.clevvertv.com/music-news/26205/jimmy-bennetts-music-video-for-over-again.html</ref>
